<HEADLINE>
<P>
WORLD IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
PHILIPPINES; 
</P>
<P>
5 PRISONERS KILLED IN ATTEMPTED JAILBREAK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A former provincial governor serving a life term for murder led an attempted 
jailbreak, and five prisoners were killed in a shoot-out with guards. Another 
prisoner and three guards were wounded during the gun battle at the National 
Penitentiary in suburban Muntinlupa, Justice Secretary Franklin Drilon said. 
The attempted break was led by former Nueva Vizcaya Gov. Orlando Dulay, who was 
serving a life term for killing three campaign workers of President Corazon 
Aquino before the February, 1986, presidential elections. 
</P>
</TEXT>
