<HEADLINE>
<P>
BUSH WILL MARK 66TH BIRTHDAY AT GOP BASH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By United Press International 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
WASHINGTON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
George Bush turns 66 today and, like Barbara Bush, who turned 65 Friday, he 
planned no family celebration. 
</P>
<P>
But Republicans were set to give him a birthday tribute with a big fund-raiser, 
the President's Dinner. 
</P>
<P>
More than 4,000 people were expected to attend the $1,500-a-plate gala. 
Proceeds will go to Republican challengers in this fall's elections, when a 
third of the Senate and the entire House will be up for grabs. 
</P>
</TEXT>
