<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: TV &amp; VIDEO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By GREG BRAXTON , Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A New 'Today': With little hoopla, lots of smiles and Willard Scott joking 
about the bald pate of Joe Garagiola, NBC's "Today" show on Monday began what 
it hopes will prove a fresh start after nearly a year of woe. 
</P>
<P>
Although heavily promoted by NBC during the weekend, the new-look "Today" was 
oddly low-key as Bryant Gumbel and co-anchor Deborah Norville welcomed 
Garagiola, the show's co-host from 1969 to 1973 and now its second co-anchor. 
There were no speeches, no recap by anchor Gumbel of the problems that led to 
Jane Pauley's departure in December, no on-air hugging by Norville. Last 
December, Norville embraced Pauley after Pauley wished her well when Pauley 
left the show. GREG BRAXTON 
</P>
</TEXT>
