MORNING REPORT: ART 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By GREG BRAXTON, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LACMA Trustees Appointed: Robert Maguire, managing partner of Maguire Thomas 
Partners real estate developers, has been elected president of the Los Angeles 
County Museum of Art's board of trustees. Maguire succeeds Daniel N. Belin, who 
will serve as chairman of the board. The museum also has appointed four new 
trustees: Robert Addison Day, chairman of Trust Co. of the West; Herbert 
Gelfand, chairman of the board of De Anza Group Inc., a real estate management 
and investment firm; Robert Halff, a retired advertising executive and screen 
writer, and Silim Zilkha, founder of Zilkha Energy Co., an oil and gas company 
in Houston. GREG BRAXTON 
</P>
