<P>
DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: TRAFFIC ACCIDENT LEADS TO VAN NUYS SHOOTING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An argument over a minor traffic accident in the parking lot of a Van Nuys 
restaurant escalated into a shooting Monday that left one man injured. Police 
were searching for the suspected gunman, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
Kenny Kingsberry, 28, of Los Angeles was shot twice in the stomach and was 
taken to an undisclosed hospital, where he was in serious but stable condition, 
Sgt. Dallas Gibson said. An unidentified man was being sought in the 2 a.m. 
shooting that occurred in the parking lot of the 94th Aero Squadron restaurant, 
on the 16300 block of Raymer Avenue, after closing time. 
</P>
<P>
"It was a dispute over a traffic accident, and while they were arguing, shots 
were fired," Gibson said. 
</P>
<P>
The gunman immediately fled. Although several patrons were leaving the 
restaurant at the time, no one could provide police with a description of the 
suspect or his car. 
</P>
