<HEADLINE>
<P>
VENTURA COUNTY NEWS ROUNDUP: CAMARILLO; 
</P>
<P>
ALTERNATE SOUGHT FOR TRANSIT COMMITEE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Camarillo is seeking a resident to represent the city as an alternate member of 
the Ventura County Citizens' Transportation Advisory Committee. 
</P>
<P>
A new alternate is needed because an alternate member was appointed recently to 
a regular seat on the board, according to City Clerk Marilyn Thiel. 
</P>
<P>
The commission, which reviews and makes recommendations on countywide 
transportation matters, meets in Ventura the second Tuesday of each month. 
Alternates are not required to attend. 
</P>
<P>
Candidates should submit a letter of interest, including relevant background 
information, to Thiel at City Hall, 601 Carmen Drive, Camarillo 93010. 
</P>
</TEXT>
