<P>
GE UNVEILS GAS TURBINE AT BRUSSELS TRADE SHOW 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
EVANDALE, Ohio 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
General Electric Co. said it has introduced a very efficient gas turbine at the 
American Society of Mechanical Engineers' trade show in Brussels. 
</P>
<P>
The company said the turbine, the LM6000, will be the most efficient, 
simple-cycle gas turbine ever built, up to 30% more efficient than any turbine 
in its power range. 
</P>
<P>
The turbine's 56,560 horsepower will be able to produce more than 40 megawatts 
of power at 42.8% efficiency, when burning natural gas and injecting steam for 
pollution control, the company said. 
