<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: ANAHEIM; 
</P>
<P>
FREEWAY CRASH KILLS PICKUP TRUCK DRIVER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
One man was killed and another injured when their pickup truck missed a curve 
and crashed on the Riverside Freeway in Anaheim, authorities said Monday. 
</P>
<P>
The driver, Gabriel Frausto, 29, of Placentia, was pronounced dead at the 
scene, while his passenger, Frank Estrada, 30, address unknown, was treated at 
Western Medical Center-Santa Ana for moderate injuries. 
</P>
<P>
The accident happened at 4:05 a.m. Sunday when the 1988 Toyota pickup, driven 
at high speed on the transition from the westbound Riverside Freeway to the 
northbound Orange Freeway, missed a curve and overturned, according to 
California Highway Patrol officials. Both occupants, who were not wearing seat 
belts, were ejected from the truck, CHP officials said. 
</P>
<P>
The CHP was investigating to determine if the driver had been drinking. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
<SUBJECT>
