<P>
INFOTECH UNVEILS NEW SOFTWARE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NEW YORK 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Infotechnology Inc. today unveiled a new product for the investment community 
that combines financial information, market data and video coverage of business 
news on a single screen. 
</P>
<P>
Infotech described the product, FNN:PRO, as an "industry first" that allows 
users to watch the video coverage of business events on a window built into the 
split screen of an IBM or IBM-compatible personal computer. 
</P>
<P>
FNN:PRO's software creates up to 16 windows on a color monitor, so that brokers 
can watch the video feed and monitor simultaneously a number of quotations and 
news services, such as UPI, Dow Jones and Reuters. 
</P>
<P>
"It is the first service that allows users to watch a video business news 
program and follow quotations at the same time," Infotech Chairman Earl Brian 
said. "That is what will lead the broker to action." 
</P>
